(88, 1, '2014-10-23 13:41:32', '2014-10-23 10:41:32', '<h2>Cloud tools</h2>\nWant to minimise the time to get your cloud infrastructure up and running and start offering your services to customers? We have the tools to get you there.\n<h2>Orchestration with Juju</h2>\nJuju is the game-changing service orchestration tool that’s the fastest way to deploy OpenStack on Ubuntu. Its libraries of ‘charms’ make it simple to deploy, configure and scale out cloud services with only a few simple commands.\n<!--more-->Whether you want to deploy OpenStack itself, a workload on public or private clouds, or even directly on bare metal using MAAS, Juju is the fastest and simplest solution.', 'Cloud tools', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-10-23 13:41:32', '2014-10-23 10:41:32', '', 1, 'http://wp.local/1-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(89, 1, '2014-10-22 17:24:33', '2014-10-22 14:24:33', '<h2>Cloud tools</h2>\r\nWant to minimise the time to get your cloud infrastructure up and running and start offering your services to customers? We have the tools to get you there.\r\n<h2>Orchestration with Juju</h2>\r\nJuju is the game-changing service orchestration tool that’s the fastest way to deploy OpenStack on Ubuntu. Its libraries of ‘charms’ make it simple to deploy, configure and scale out cloud services with only a few simple commands.\r\n<!--more-->Whether you want to deploy OpenStack itself, a workload on public or private clouds, or even directly on bare metal using MAAS, Juju is the fastest and simplest solution.<!--more-->', 'Cloud tools', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-22 17:24:33', '2014-10-22 14:24:33', '', 1, 'http://wp.local/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
