(122, 1, '2014-10-23 11:33:07', '2014-10-23 08:33:07', '<p style="text-align: justify;">WordPress is a <a title="Free and open source" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open_source">f</a>ree and open source blogging tool and a content management system (CMS) based on PHP and MySQL. Features include a plugin architecture and a template system. WordPress was used by more than 22.0% of the top 10 million websites as of August 2013. WordPress is the most popular blogging system in use on the Web,at more than 60 million websites.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It was first released on May 27, 2003, by its founders, Matt Mullenweg and Mike Little, as a fork of b2/cafelog. The license under which WordPress software is released is the GPLv2 (or later) from the Free Software Foundation.</p>', 'About WordPress', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '100-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-23 11:33:07', '2014-10-23 08:33:07', '', 100, 'http://wp.local/100-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
